---
import Avatar from './Avatar.astro';
---

<section id="about" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-white/50">
	<div class="container mx-auto">
		<h2 class="text-3xl text-arctic font-bold text-center mb-2 tracking-wide reveal">
			About Me
		</h2>
		<div class="w-12 h-0.5 bg-glacier mx-auto mb-12 reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.1s"></div>

		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.2s">
			<div
				class="bg-white border border-mist/60 p-8 md:p-10"
				style="box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(52, 89, 136, 0.06), 0 1px 4px rgba(52, 89, 136, 0.04);"
			>
				<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 items-center md:items-start">
					<div class="flex-shrink-0 flex flex-col items-center gap-6">
						<Avatar src="/portfolio-astro/avatar.jpeg" size="medium" />
						<img
							src="/portfolio-astro/sword.png"
							alt="Sword"
							class="h-64 md:h-80 object-contain opacity-80"
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="flex-1 space-y-5 text-slate leading-relaxed">
						<p class="text-base md:text-lg">
							From Argentina to Ireland — I've spent the past several years building full-stack
							web applications, from pixel-precise interfaces to resilient backend systems.
							I care about clean architecture, thoughtful APIs, and code that reads as well
							as it performs.
						</p>

						<p class="text-base md:text-lg">
							Born in Argentina, I sharpened my craft across a range of domains before the
							winds of opportunity brought me to Dublin, Ireland — a city of misty coastlines
							and a thriving tech scene that I've been proud to be part of ever since.
						</p>

						<p class="text-base md:text-lg">
							Outside the keyboard, open landscapes give me perspective. Whether it's the
							wild coast of Connemara, a long trail through the mountains, or simply the
							quiet expanse of an overcast sky — those moments of scale and stillness shape
							how I approach complex problems in software.
						</p>

						<p class="text-base md:text-lg">
							Always building, always learning. The next summit is always worth it.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
